<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-19T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-19T02:00:00-05:00" n="753" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d753">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/6378: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Peck</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-19T15:00:00+08:00">May 19, 1937—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 19—8:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>211. Our 209, May 18, 10 a.m. An officer of the Embassy has been informed
                            by the French Ambassador that an agreement for a loan of Chinese dollars
                            24,500,000 for the construction of the Chengtu-Chungking Railway was
                            recently signed in Paris between the Banque Franco-Chinoise and Chinese
                            representatives acting for the Ministry of Railways and the China
                            Development Finance Corporation.</p>
                        <p>Sent to the Department; by mail to Peiping, Shanghai, Tokyo.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>